Five sub-orbital rotations with
every 360-degree turn

Stellar’s orbital action solves these problems by creating five sub-circular rotations with every 360-degree turn of the brush-head.

This unique motion not only cleans more evenly, it does a superior job of cleaning the critical space between teeth and on the complex top-surfaces of teeth.

Today's electric toothbrushes that oscillate
or spin have a serious design flaw: the bristles on the outer edge move at high
speed, while the innermost bristles hardly move at all.
This can lead to overbrushing along the gum line and not enough brushing on the critical, complex top surfaces of teeth, especially molars.
